Ghanaian dancehall artiste, Stonebwoy, has urged other African artists to give it up for Nigeria following the Grammy wins of Wizkid and Burna Boy. Stonebwoy, on his social page, wrote: “With all due respect let all other African Nations give it up for Nigeria for their constant efforts in holding the mantle for Africa when it comes to entertainment on the global scene. Congratulations for holding it down at the Grammys.” Wizkid won Best Music Video for his collaboration with Beyoncé on Brown Skin Girl while Burna Boy won in the Best Global Music Album category.